.TH "omap_gem_dumb_create" 9 "omap_gem_dumb_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap_gem_dumb_create \- create a dumb buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap_gem_dumb_create
.BI "(struct drm_file *file "  ","
.BI "struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_mode_create_dumb *args "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
our client file
.IP "dev" 12
our device
.IP "args" 12
the requested arguments copied from userspace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a buffer suitable for use for a frame buffer of the
form described by user space. Give userspace a handle by which
to reference it.
